data.text:
Frederick II of Prussia (24 January 1712 CE – 17 August 1786 CE) was King of the ancient nation state of Prussia on Old Earth from 1740 CE to his death. He became known as Frederick the Great ("Friedrich der Große" in German) because of the growth of Prussia's size and importance during his reign.

He was one of the last heads of state who personally led troops in combat.

Gustav Anderman I, founder and first Emperor of the Andermani Empire, reportedly believed himself to be a reincarnation of Frederick the Great. (HH2)

The Solarian League Navy destroyer SLNS Frederick II was named after him. (CS2)
